# ⚙ Virtual Environment Setup

Create virtual environment

```
python -m venv .venv
```

Activate (Windows)

```
.venv\Scripts\activate
```

Deactivate

```
deactivate
```

Upgrade pip

```
python -m pip install --upgrade pip
```

---

# 📦 Required Packages

Install required libraries

```
pip install langchain
pip install langgraph
pip install langchain-core
pip install langchain-community
pip install langchain-ollama
pip install playwright
pip install typing_extensions
```

Install Playwright browser

```
playwright install
```

(Optional)

```
pip freeze > requirements.txt
```

Install from requirements

```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

# 🦙 Ollama Setup

Install Ollama.

Start Ollama server.

Pull model

```
ollama pull qwen2.5:0.5b
```

or

```
ollama pull qwen3:4b
```

Verify

```
ollama list
```

---

# 🤖 Agent Workflow

```
User Prompt
      │
      ▼
LLM understands instruction
      │
      ▼
Chooses appropriate Tool
      │
      ▼
Playwright executes action
      │
      ▼
Capture Screenshot
      │
      ▼
Log execution
      │
      ▼
Generate HTML Report
```

---

# 🔧 Browser Automation Tools

Current tools include:

* Open URL
* Click Element
* Fill Text
* Take Screenshot
* Browser Navigation
* Window Management
* Dropdown Selection (planned)
* Checkbox Handling (planned)
* Frame Switching (planned)
* Popup Handling (planned)
* DOM Access (planned)
* Web Element Discovery (planned)

Adding a new tool only requires creating a new LangChain `@tool` function and registering it with the agent.

---

# 📸 Screenshot Capture

The framework captures browser screenshots during execution.

Screenshots are stored under:

```
reports/screenshots/
```

These screenshots are linked in the generated HTML report for easy debugging.

---

# 📊 HTML Reporting

After execution, the framework generates an HTML report containing:

* Execution Time
* Tool Name
* Action Performed
* Status
* Details
* Screenshot Reference

Report location:

```
reports/report.html
```

---

# ❌ Failure Analysis Agent

A dedicated failure analysis capability helps investigate execution failures by:

* Reviewing execution logs.
* Inspecting browser actions.
* Identifying failed tool calls.
* Capturing failure screenshots.
* Summarizing probable root causes.

This enables quicker debugging compared to manually inspecting automation logs.

---

# ▶ Running the Framework

```
python app.py
```

Execution flow

```
Start Browser

↓

Initialize AI Agent

↓

Receive User Prompt

↓

LLM selects tools

↓

Playwright executes actions

↓

Capture screenshots

↓

Generate HTML Report

↓

Close Browser
```

---

# 💬 Example Prompt

```
Open https://practicetestautomation.com/practice-test-login/

Enter username as student

Enter password as Password123

Click Login

Capture screenshots after each step.
```

---

# 🧩 Core Components

### Browser Manager

Responsible for:

* Starting browser
* Managing browser context
* Creating pages
* Closing browser

---

### Workflow

Responsible for:

* Initializing LangGraph Agent
* Registering tools
* Connecting LLM
* Executing prompts

---

### Tools

Responsible for browser operations including:

* Click
* Fill
* Navigation
* Screenshot
* Browser controls

---

### Report Manager

Responsible for:

* Logging execution
* Maintaining step history
* Recording screenshots
* Recording execution status

---

### Report Generator

Responsible for creating the HTML execution report after test completion.

---

# 🔄 Extending the Framework

New automation capabilities can be added easily by creating additional LangChain tools such as:

* Hover
* Drag and Drop
* Double Click
* Keyboard Actions
* Mouse Actions
* JavaScript Execution
* File Upload
* Download Verification
* API Validation
* Visual Testing

---


# ⚠ Troubleshooting

### Playwright not installed

```
playwright install
```

---

### Browser does not launch

Check:

* Playwright installation
* Browser binaries
* Headless configuration

---

### Ollama model unavailable

Verify

```
ollama list
```

Pull the required model

```
ollama pull qwen2.5:0.5b
```

---

### Virtual environment not activated

Windows

```
.venv\Scripts\activate
```

